313520":null,"customfield_12311020":null,"duedate":null,"customfield_12310250":null,"progress":{"progress":0,"total":0},"comment":{"comments":[{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12342593/comment/12410505","id":"12410505","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=joerg%40myndian.de","name":"joerg@myndian.de","key":"joerg@myndian.de","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Jörg Gottschling","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"body":"Perhaps Validate.notEmpty should also throw NullArgumentException if the\nArgument was null.","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=joerg%40myndian.de","name":"joerg@myndian.de","key":"joerg@myndian.de","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Jörg Gottschling","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"created":"2005-10-01T22:22:53.000+0000","updated":"2005-10-01T22:22:53.000+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12342593/comment/12410506","id":"12410506","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=jwcarman","name":"jwcarman","key":"jwcarman","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"James Carman","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"body":"What is NullArgumentException?  Do you mean NullPointerException?","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=jwcarman","name":"jwcarman","key":"jwcarman","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"James Carman","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"created":"2005-10-02T00:24:45.000+0000","updated":"2005-10-02T00:24:45.000+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12342593/comment/12410507","id":"12410507","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=jwcarman","name":"jwcarman","key":"jwcarman","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"James Carman","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"body":"Changing these methods to throw a different exception type could break existing\ncode that depends on the fact that they throw IllegalArgumentException.  What if\nsomeone (even if it's not suggested) puts a try/catch around a call to\nValidate.notNull() which catches IllegalArgumentException?  For most cases\nyou're not really supposed to catch runtime exceptions, but that doesn't mean\nthat it's not done.","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=jwcarman","name":"jwcarman","key":"jwcarman","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"James Carman","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"created":"2005-10-02T00:29:45.000+0000","updated":"2005-10-02T00:29:45.000+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12342593/comment/12410508","id":"12410508","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=joerg%40myndian.de","name":"joerg@myndian.de","key":"joerg@myndian.de","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Jörg Gottschling","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"body":"For NullArgumentException see here:\nhttp://jakarta.apache.org/commons/lang/api/org/apache/commons/lang/NullArgumentException.html\n\nIt's in the same package als Validate and a subclass of\nIllegalArgumentException, so it is no Problem to change this.","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=joerg%40myndian.de","name":"joerg@myndian.de","key":"joerg@myndian.de","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Jörg Gottschling","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"created":"2005-10-02T02:49:09.000+0000","updated":"2005-10-02T02:49:09.000+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12342593/comment/12410509","id":"12410509","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=jwcarman","name":"jwcarman","key":"jwcarman","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"James Carman","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"body":"Ahhh.  I was looking in the exception package and didn't see it.  This shouldn't\ncause any problems, then, I wouldn't think.  Good idea!","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=jwcarman","name":"jwcarman","key":"jwcarman","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"James Carman","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"created":"2005-10-02T11:20:23.000+0000","updated":"2005-10-02T11:20:23.000+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12342593/comment/12410510","id":"12410510","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=joerg%40myndian.de","name":"joerg@myndian.de","key":"joerg@myndian.de","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Jörg Gottschling","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"body":"Hm, but there would be little difference in the use of\nValidate.notNull(Object,String) and the Methods notEmpty with take an message as\nsecond argument. At the moment I write something like:\n\npublic void foo(Object bar){\n  Validate.notNull(bar, \"bar was null\");\n  //other code\n}\n\n\nBut if notNull would throw an NullArgumentException you should write \n\npublic void foo(Object bar){\n  Validate.notNull(bar, \"bar\");\n  //other code\n}\n\nOr you would get \"bar was null must not be null.\" as message. :-)\n\n\nBTW: Perhaps I want to provide some methods to this class (Validate). What do I\nhave to do? (Or should I create an issue for every new method?)","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=joerg%40myndian.de","name":"joerg@myndian.de","key":"joerg@myndian.de","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Jörg Gottschling","active":true,"timeZone":"Etc/UTC"},"created":"2005-10-03T02:38:05.000+0000","updated":"2005-10-03T02:38:05.000+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12342593/comment/12410511","id":"12410511","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=bayard","name":"bayard","key":"bayard","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Henri Yandell","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"body":"Sorry for lateness in replying Jörg. If you still wanted to do such, multiple\nattachments to the one issue is fine. If the attachments started to involve\ndifferent classes, packages, or problems, then I'd be tempted to kick off a new\nissue.","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=bayard","name":"bayard","key":"bayard","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Henri Yandell","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"created":"2006-04-15T06:21:12.000+0000","updated":"2006-04-15T06:21:12.000+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12342593/comment/12410512","id":"12410512","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=bayard","name":"bayard","key":"bayard","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Henri Yandell","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"body":"API change, so targetted for 3.0 (which hopefully will be pretty quickly after\n2.2). ","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=bayard","name":"bayard","key":"bayard","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Henri Yandell","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"created":"2006-04-24T14:06:19.000+0000","updated":"2006-04-24T14:06:19.000+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12342593/comment/12444520","id":"12444520","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=bayard","name":"bayard","key":"bayard","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Henri Yandell","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"body":"The only problem with this is in the messages. The NullArgumentException automatically adds \" must not be null\" to the end of any message passed up to it (ACK). In Validate we receive the message to print out, so having \" must not be null\" on the end becomes very daft. Credit to whomever wrote the unit tests that failed; otherwise I wouldn't have noticed.\n\nWe should also change the noNullElements methods if we do change the notNull ones, but I think the gain here is not worth the pain.\n\nI'm +1 to WONTFIX this.","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=bayard","name":"bayard","key":"bayard","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatar